   104→## Installation and Docs
   105→
   106→Install using `go get github.com/hashicorp/go-multierror`.
   107→
   108→Full documentation is available at
   109→https://pkg.go.dev/github.com/hashicorp/go-multierror
   110→
   111→### Requires go version 1.13 or newer
   112→
   113→`go-multierror` requires go version 1.13 or newer. Go 1.13 introduced
   114→[error wrapping](https://golang.org/doc/go1.13#error_wrapping), which
   115→this library takes advantage of.
   116→
   117→If you need to use an earlier version of go, you can use the
   129→## Usage
   130→
   131→go-multierror is easy to use and purposely built to be unobtrusive in
   132→existing Go applications/libraries that may not be aware of it.
